Program: Discovery
Title: The brains of astronauts
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrx3p
Last Broadcast Date: 26 March 1998
Inside the brains of astronauts and dolphins. Those about to go into space are having their brains monitored using a doppler ultrasound developed using dolphins. Also in the programme Jamaica's coral reefs and treating diabetes by mouth. Presenter: Graham Easton.